stylometry: For my group project we analyzed Jennifer & Co Salon and Spa to see how each area of their operations (nails, tanning, hair and makeup, and the spa) determining how many servers they would need to meet their incoming customers. We made several suggestions to the management on how many servers to keep in each area (determined by using the M/M/s template) from the analysis we made focusing on the utilization of servers, queuing costs, and total costs to name a few. From the information we gleaned using our models, management will be able to try out the different changes we suggested to see how they fare in the workplace. Unfortunately, excel macros are unable to show every possibility for this model and there may be unforseen variables we did not consider leading to our calculations being incorrect for the work place, but the only way to find out our model's efficiency is to attempt it on the floor.
